HEADWORD: Wellington boot
<hw>Wel"ling*ton boot</hw>. <ety>[After the Duke of
<etsep>Wellington</etsep>.]</ety> <def>A riding boot for men, the front
of which came above the knee; also, a similar shorter boot worn under
the trousers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wellingtonia</ent>⟦br⟧
